#+begin_quote
Suppose $T \in  \mathcal{L}(V)$ and $U$ is a subspace of $V$. Prove that $U$ is invariant under $T$ iff $U^\bot$ is invariant under $T^*$.
#+end_quote

For all $u \in  $

This implies that both directions, since $U = U^{\perp ^\perp }$ and $T = (T^*)^*$.
